.TH NQIFTOP 1 "2026-06-10" "qiftop 0.2.4" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
nqiftop \- ncurses real\-time network traffic monitor (qiftop)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B nqiftop
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B nqiftop
is the terminal (ncurses) front\-end of qiftop. It presents the same two
live views as the GUI \(em
.B Interfaces
and
.B Connections
\(em over SSH or on a headless box, with no X11/Wayland dependency.
.PP
Like
.BR qiftop (1),
it probes for the privileged
.BR qiftop\-agent (8)
on D\-Bus and consumes statistics from it as an unprivileged client; if no
agent is reachable it falls back to an in\-process capture backend (which
needs root for per\-connection data). The active source is shown at the
right of the title bar alongside the aggregate throughput
.RB ( \(*S
RX\(da TX\(ua) and the current gauge scale.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-i ", " \-\-interval " " \fIms\fR
Poll/refresh interval in milliseconds (default 1000). Values are applied to
both the data source and display smoothing; the runtime Settings panel uses
100 ms to 10 s bounds. An explicit command\-line value overrides the saved
one.
.TP
.B \-\-theme " " \fIname\fR
Colour theme:
.BR dark ", " light ", " colorblind ", " mono
(default
.BR dark ).
Cycle live with
.BR z .
.TP
.B \-\-view " " \fItab\fR
Initial tab:
.B interfaces
or
.BR connections .
Default is the last\-used tab.
.TP
.B \-\-group " " \fImode\fR
Group the Connections view:
.BR off ", " interface ", " process ", " container .
Default is the last\-used mode. Cycle live with
.BR g .
.TP
.B \-\-session
Talk to the agent on the
.B session
bus instead of the system bus (development).
.TP
.B \-\-no\-agent
Skip the agent and capture in\-process (needs root).
.TP
.B \-\-verbose
Diagnostics to stderr.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help ", " \-v ", " \-\-version
Show help / version and exit.
.SH INTERACTIVE KEYS
.SS Navigation and views
.TP
.BR j ", " k ", " \(da ", " \(ua
Move the current\-line cursor down / up. Group headers are skipped in
grouped Connections views.
.TP
.BR PgUp ", " PgDn ", " ^U ", " ^D
Move the cursor by a full / half page.
.TP
.BR Home ", " End ", " G
Jump to the top / bottom.
.TP
.BR Tab ", " 1 ", " 2
Switch view (Interfaces / Connections).
.TP
.BR Enter ", " Space ", " l ", " \(->
Open a modal detail inspector for the selected row. For connections it shows
the 5\-tuple, direction, interface, TCP state, process and container
attribution, rates, totals and packets; for interfaces it shows type,
addresses, MTU, oper\-state, errors and drops. While the detail panel is
open,
.BR j / k
or the up/down arrows browse to the next/previous row; any other key closes
it.
.TP
.BR h ", " \(<-
Reserved in the main table (no inline collapse; details are modal). In
Settings, Fields and other panels, vim keys and arrows navigate or adjust
where shown in the panel footer.
.SS Sorting and grouping
.TP
.B s
Cycle the sort column.
.TP
.B f
Open the Fields panel to pick the sort column and direction.
.TP
.B r
Reverse the sort order.
.TP
.B g
Cycle connection grouping (off / interface / process / container).
.SS Filtering, display and export
.TP
.B /
Edit a Connections filter expression (see
.BR "FILTER LANGUAGE" ).
.B Enter
applies,
.B Esc
cancels editing; when a filter is active,
.B Esc
clears it.
.TP
.B p
Pause / resume the display. Pause is a true snapshot freeze: the visible
rows, sort order and cursor stop changing and the smoothing timer stops,
while the capture pipeline continues updating in the background. Unpausing
returns immediately to fresh live data.
.TP
.B w
Export the current view to a timestamped CSV file in the current working
directory:
.IR qiftop\-interfaces\-YYYYMMDD\-HHMMSS.csv
or
.IR qiftop\-connections\-YYYYMMDD\-HHMMSS.csv .
When paused, the frozen snapshot is exported.
.TP
.B z
Cycle the colour theme.
.TP
.B S
.RB ( "or " F2 )
Open the Settings panel (theme, grouping, poll interval, gauge, direction
colours, DNS resolution, UDP aggregation, rate smoothing). Use
.BR "\(ua\(da" / "j" / "k"
to move and
.BR "\(<-" / "\(->" / "h" / "l" / "Space"
to change a value.
.TP
.BR ? ", " F1
Show the key\-binding help overlay.
.TP
.B a
Show the About panel (application/library version, data source, Qt and OS
version, terminal capability).
.TP
.B q
Quit.
.PP
View, sort columns, grouping, theme, poll interval and every toggle are
persisted and restored on the next launch (unless overridden on the
command line).
.SH FILTER LANGUAGE
The Connections filter is a small boolean expression language (shared with
the GUI). Combine predicates with
.BR and ", " or ", " not
and parentheses.
.PP
.B String fields:
.IR proto ", " src ", " dst ", " host ", " iface ", " family ", " direction ", "
.IR comm ", " runtime ", " container ", " chain_has .
.br
.B Numeric fields:
.IR sport ", " dport ", " port ", " bytes_in / out / total ", "
.IR pkts_in / out / total ", " rate_in / out / total ", " pid ", " uid .
.PP
.B Operators:
.RB ` : '
(string substring / numeric ==),
.RB ` = ' " / " ` != '
(exact / negated),
.RB ` ~ '
(regex),
.RB ` < ' " " ` <= ' " " ` > ' " " ` >= '
(numeric).
Numeric values accept IEC/SI byte suffixes
.RB ( K ", " Ki ", " M ", " Mi ", " G ", " Gi ", " T ", " Ti ).
.PP
.B Examples:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
proto:tcp and port=443
rate_total > 1Mi
host ~ amazonaws and not dport:53
runtime:docker and bytes_out > 100Ki
pid=0
.fi
.RE
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/qiftop/nqiftop.conf
Per\-user nqiftop settings (\fBQSettings\fR INI), separate from the GUI's
.IR qiftop.conf .
.TP
.I ./qiftop-interfaces-YYYYMMDD-HHMMSS.csv
.TQ
.I ./qiftop-connections-YYYYMMDD-HHMMSS.csv
CSV exports written by
.BR w .
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR qiftop (1),
.BR qiftop\-agent (8),
.BR qiftop\-agent.conf (5),
.BR iftop (8)
.SH HOMEPAGE
https://github.com/TheCleaners/qiftop
.SH BUGS
Report issues at https://github.com/TheCleaners/qiftop/issues
